doc.after: The first production Sukhoi Superjet was delivered to Armavia on 19 April 2011. The handover ceremony was held at Zvartnots International Airport in Yerevan on the same day.[130] The aircraft was named "Yuri Gagarin", after the first man to venture into space almost exactly 50 years before.[131] Armavia planned to operate its Superjet 100 on flights between Yerevan, Sochi and Ukrainian cities,[130] including Odessa and Simferopol. The airline had expected to receive its second Superjet in June 2011.[123]
